BFN 

  [Text] In South Africa, Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva proposed 
a coalition government no matter what candidate or political 
party wins the upcoming elections. 
  Lula is visiting South Africa as the presidential candidate 
for the Workers Party [PT]. He has met with President Nelson 
Mandela, South African congressmen, and entrepreneurs. Lula 
said if the PT wins the elections, he will intensify trade and 
cultural relations between Brazil and South Africa. 

